# PropPredict — Cursor rules

## Project overview

PropPredict is a **single Next.js 15 application** (App Router) deployable on Vercel. There is no separate backend — all API routes live under `app/api/`.

- **Stack**: Next.js 15, React 19, Tailwind CSS v4, Prisma (PostgreSQL), in-memory LMSR trading engine
- **Multi-tenant**: firm-scoped branding via middleware + Prisma `Tenant` model
- **Provisioning**: `PropFirmAccount`, `ChallengeConfig`, `TraderDemoAccount` (see `prisma/schema.prisma`)
- **Polymarket**: TypeScript CLOB integration in `lib/polymarket/`

## Structure

```
app/           # Pages and API routes
components/    # UI components
lib/           # Core utilities, store, polymarket, auth, db
services/      # Business logic (markets, portfolio, orders)
hooks/         # Client hooks
types/         # Shared TypeScript types
prisma/        # Database schema (Tenant, User, PropFirmAccount, …)
middleware.ts  # Tenant resolution
```

## API routes

All backend logic runs as Next.js Route Handlers under `app/api/`:

- `/api/auth/*` — JWT login, register, me
- `/api/markets`, `/api/orders`, `/api/portfolio`, `/api/journal`
- `/api/polymarket/*` — Polymarket CLOB market discovery
- `/api/tenant`, `/api/admin/tenant` — white-label config
- `/api/platform/*` — Super Admin endpoints

## Conventions

- Frontend calls `/api/...` only — never external backend URLs
- Match existing code style; keep diffs focused
- `npm run build` must pass before shipping
- Branch prefix for agent work: `cursor/<name>-224f`
